ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: After taking this class you will be able to understand books that few other people in the world are able to understand.

The course provides a great intro to traditional and contemporary issues in modal metaphysics. Decent background in logic--not only baby logic, but ideally some modal logic--is preferable; otherwise the pace and additional workload could be steep. Although important issues in modal metaphysics-like essentialism, dispositionalism etc.-are left out, the course provides a very goodstarting point for finding one's one way into these debates. Definitely recommended.
